events.text:
Day of Hunger
Food grows scarce.
I’ve stockpiled just enough moon carrots to hold me over for a few more days.
The moon bunny has grown ravenous.
I scamper out as soon as I awaken to collect what few remain untouched by its nocturnal grazing.
I have still yet to see it.
It must be underground sucking the moon carrots down its great gullet from beneath.
I’m surprised I haven’t drawn its attention yet.
Surely it must be able to hear the pounding of my heart even through the thin atmosphere.
Even this torturous soundtrack pumping through my headphones can’t drown it out.
What is this and why can’t I turn it off?
The same tune over and over.
You guys can hear this, right?
Who picked this track?
They should be ashamed of themselves.
I wish I knew how to at least switch channels.
I could go for some Beatles or Bon Jovi, or nails on a chalkboard.
Literally anything that isn’t this.
Poor taste in music aside, I should go out and try to grab a few more moon carrots before the moon bunny inhales them.
